## Prompt

We just completed L0 summary record-shape validation. The current main branch validates real L0ChunkSummary.to_dict JSON records at create_l0_chunk write time and provider L0 load time. Malformed provider L0 records are treated as unavailable/not_found; detailed malformed-store diagnostics were explicitly deferred. The next target should be one small vertical slice. Compare these options: A) add malformed L0 store diagnostics without changing existing provider-summary drop reasons, B) guarded explicit L0 context-pack inclusion/rendering, C) L0 store listing/index command, D) stop L0 work and move back to admission/ranking policy. Choose the safest next target for AI-Lab's ontology-first design, explain risks, and recommend exact acceptance tests.

